9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 399, L.D. 631, “An Act to Allow a
10 Home Distiller to Distill and Share Homemade Spirituous Liquor”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in §1358 in subsection 2 in the 3rd line (page 1, line 17 in
12 L.D.) by striking out the following: "consumption," and inserting the following:
13 'consumption or'
14 Amend the bill in section 1 in §1358 in subsection 2 in the last 2 lines (page 1, lines 18
15 and 19 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "or shipping the product to the owner's family
16 members and friends"
17 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
18 number to read consecutively.
19 SUMMARY
2200 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, removes the provision
2211 in the bill allowing distilled spirits to be shipped to the home distillery owner's family
2222 members and friends.
